 |last=Munro |date=October 21, 2007 |accessdate=January 15, 2018 |quote=Indeed, the original plans for the Scarborough line were based on CLRV operation. However, the engineers working on this had only a vague grasp of transit basics, and they determined that the new cars had to travel at up to 70mph (roughly 110kph) for suburban operations. ... Further problems ensued because the wheels chosen for these vehicles were incompatible with our track, notably at switches where cars tended to derail. This problem was fixed, eventually, along with the worst of the noise and vibration issues by a change to the type of wheel we now see on the CLRVs, itself a descendent of the PCC design. |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180116081325/https://stevemunro.ca/2007/10/21/a-short-history-of-the-clrv/ |archive-date=January 16, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"TTC-2009-02-18\">{{cite web |url=https://www.ttc.ca/TTC_Accessibility/Public_Forum_on_Accessible_Transit/2009/Accessible_Transit_Services_Plan_2008_Status_Report_and_Stat.jsp |title=Accessible Transit Services Plan: 2008 Status Report, and Status of Accessibility Standards |publisher=[[Toronto Transit Commission]] |date={{date|2009-02-18|mdy}} |accessdate={{date|2018-10-30|mdy}} |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181031052725/https://www.ttc.ca/TTC_Accessibility/Public_Forum_on_Accessible_Transit/2009/Accessible_Transit_Services_Plan_2008_Status_Report_and_Stat.jsp |archive-date=October 31, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Torontoist-2007-12-28\">{{cite web |url=https://torontoist.com/2007/12/hero_ttc_automa/ |title=Hero: TTC Automated Announcements |publisher=The Torontoist |first=Marc |last=Lostracco |date={{date|2007-12-28|mdy}} |accessdate={{date|2018-10-30|mdy}} |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181031091141/https://torontoist.com/2007/12/hero_ttc_automa/ |archive-date=October 31, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"TO-2016-02-25\">{{cite web |url=https://www.toronto.ca/legdocs/mmis/2016/ex/bgrd/backgroundfile-92670.pdf |title=2016 Accessibility Plan Status Report |publisher=[[City of Toronto government|City of Toronto]] |author=[[Toronto Transit Commission]] |date={{date|2016-02-25|mdy}} |accessdate={{date|2018-10-30|mdy}} |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181031091133/https://www.toronto.ca/legdocs/mmis/2016/ex/bgrd/backgroundfile-92670.pdf |archive-date=October 31, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"CityNews-2006-07-26\">{{cite web |url=https://toronto.citynews.ca/2006/07/26/first-air-conditioned-ttc-streetcar-unveiled/ |title=First Air Conditioned TTC Streetcar Unveiled |newspaper=[[CityNews]] |date={{date|2006-07-26|mdy}} |accessdate={{date|2018-10-30|mdy}} |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181031052811/https://toronto.citynews.ca/2006/07/26/first-air-conditioned-ttc-streetcar-unveiled/ |archive-date={{date|2018-10-31|mdy}} }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"SteveMunro-2006-07-21\">{{cite web |url=https://stevemunro.ca/2006/07/21/the-air-conditioned-streetcar/ |title=The Air Conditioned Streetcar |publisher=[[Steve Munro]] |first=Steve |last=Munro |date=July 21, 2006 |accessdate=January 15, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180116081321/https://stevemunro.ca/2006/07/21/the-air-conditioned-streetcar/ |archive-date=January 16, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"SteveMunro-2018-09-05\">{{cite web |url=https://stevemunro.ca/2018/09/01/the-decline-of-service-capacity-on-501-queen/ |title=The Decline of Service Capacity on 501 Queen |publisher=[[Steve Munro]] |first=Steve |last=Munro |date={{date|2018-09-05|mdy}} |accessdate={{date|2018-11-02|mdy}} |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181014091555/https://stevemunro.ca/2018/09/01/the-decline-of-service-capacity-on-501-queen/ |archive-date=October 14, 2018 |url-status=live }} See quoted reply from Brad Ross.</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"TheStar-2016-05-13\">{{cite news |url=https://www.thestar.com/news/gta/2016/05/13/ttc-staff-put-in-careful-hour-keeping-an-aging-fleet-stay-on-track.html |title=TTC staff 'perform miracles' keeping aging streetcar fleet on track |newspaper=[[Toronto Star]] |author=Ben Spurr |date=May 13, 2016 |accessdate=May 13, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160515110116/https://www.thestar.com/news/gta/2016/05/13/ttc-staff-put-in-careful-hour-keeping-an-aging-fleet-stay-on-track.html |archive-date=May 15, 2016 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Metro-2015-06-16\">{{cite web |url=http://metronews.ca/news/toronto/1399681/ttc-upgrading-some-streetcars-crushing-others/ |title=TTC upgrading some streetcars, crushing others |work=MetroNews |first=Chris |last=Bateman |date=June 16, 2015 |accessdate=June 17, 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150620025517/http://metronews.ca/news/toronto/1399681/ttc-upgrading-some-streetcars-crushing-others/ |archive-date=June 20, 2015}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"TTC-2015-10-15\">{{cite news |url=https://www.ttc.ca/News/2015/October/1015_streetcar_rebuild.jsp/ |title=Newly-restored TTC streetcar enters service |newspaper=Toronto Transit Commission |date=October 15, 2015 |accessdate=October 22, 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161112085108/https://www.ttc.ca/News/2015/October/1015_streetcar_rebuild.jsp |archivedate=November 12, 2016}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"TheStar-2018-11-12\">{{cite news |url=https://www.thestar.com/news/gta/2018/11/12/toronto-pulls-plug-on-program-created-to-extend-life-of-older-streetcars-after-it-exceeds-budget-and-falls-short-of-target.html |title=TTC spent $26{{nbsp}}million to save 30 aging streetcars. But majority of the vehicles are still in the garage in need of more repairs |newspaper=[[Toronto Star]] |first=Ben |last=Spurr |date={{date|2018-11-12|mdy}} |accessdate={{date|2018-11-13|mdy}} |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181113042259/https://www.thestar.com/news/gta/2018/11/12/toronto-pulls-plug-on-program-created-to-extend-life-of-older-streetcars-after-it-