.blogto.com/city/2014/08/the_story_of_the_last_new_streetcar_launch_in_toronto/ |title=The story of the last new streetcar launch in Toronto |publisher=[[BlogTO]] |author=Chris Bateman |date=August 19, 2014 |page= |location= |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140821020856/https://www.blogto.com/city/2014/08/the_story_of_the_last_new_streetcar_launch_in_toronto/ |archivedate=August 21, 2014 |accessdate=August 20, 2014 |url-status=live}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category multi|Canadian Light Rail Vehicles in Toronto|Articulated Light Rail Vehicles in Toronto}}\n* [https://transit.toronto.on.ca/streetcar/4503.shtml The Canadian Light Rail Vehicles (The CLRVs)]\n* [https://transit.toronto.on.ca/streetcar/4504.shtml The Articulated Light Rail Vehicles (The ALRVs)]\n* [https://cptdb.ca/wiki/index.php?title=Toronto_Transit_Commission_4000-4005,_4010-4199 Toronto Transit Commission 4000\u20134005, 4010\u20134199] CLRV roster\n* [https://cptdb.ca/wiki/index.php/Toronto_Transit_Commission_4200-4251 Toronto Transit Commission 4200\u20134251] ALRV roster\n* {{YouTube|EvtUBS43E9M|CLRV 4000 End of Line}} depicting retired CLRV 4000 being loaded on a flatbed at the Leslie Barns\n* {{YouTube|1unl5TaJW6E|\"Bendy\" streetcars take their last rides as TTC vehicles}}: Last official runs of the ALRV\n\n{{TTC rolling stock}}\n{{TTC}}\n\n[[Category:Toronto streetcar vehicles]]\n[[Category:Articulated passenger trains]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Type of Canadian streetcar}}\n{{redirect2|CLRV|ALRV}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=June 2018}}\n{{Infobox train\n| name = CLRV\n| image = [[File:CLRV 4059 Glamour Shot.jpg|frameless|upright=1.14]]\n| caption = A [[506 Carlton]] CLRV car crosses the Main Street Bridge in 2008.\n| manufacturer =  L1: [[Schweizerische Industrie Gesellschaft|SIG]]<br>L2: [[Urban Transportation Development Corporation|UTDC]]\n| fleetnumbers =  L1: 4000\u20134005<br>L2: 4010\u20134199\n| operator =  [[Toronto Transit Commission]] (former, all retired