n| 4207\n| Toronto Transit Commission\n| Toronto, ON\n| Operational\n| Preserved as a heritage vehicle for future special events, such as charters and parades.<ref name=\"TTC-2019-08-29\"/>\n|}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Light rail vehicle]]\n\n=== Similar vehicles ===\n* [[US Standard Light Rail Vehicle]], a similar, though unsuccessful, attempt to build a standardized PCC successor in the US.\n* [[Kawasaki Heavy Industries Rolling Stock Company]] K LRV for [[SEPTA]] to replace PCC streetcars and similar to the CLRV\n* [[Santa Clara VTA Light-rail]], which used a somewhat similar car design also produced by UTDC.\n\n== References ==\n===Citations===\n{{Reflist\n|refs=\n\n<ref name=\"TT-CLRV\">{{cite web |url=https://transit.toronto.on.ca/streetcar/4503.shtml |title=The Canadian Light Rail Vehicles (The CLRVs) |publisher=Transit Toronto |first=James |last=Bow |date=December 3, 2017 |accessdate=January 11, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171227235322/http://transit.toronto.on.ca/streetcar/4503.shtml |archive-date=December 27, 2017 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"TT-ALRV\">{{cite web |url=https://transit.toronto.on.ca/streetcar/4504.shtml |title=The Articulated Light Rail Vehicles (The ALRVs) |publisher=Transit Toronto |first=James |last=Bow |date=January 30, 2017 |accessdate=January 11, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180112160156/https://transit.toronto.on.ca/streetcar/4504.shtml |archive-date=January 12, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"RwyAge-2018-01-05\">{{cite web |url=http://www.railwayage.com/index.php/passenger/light-rail/the-car-that-saved-torontos-streetcars.html |title=The car that saved Toronto's streetcars |publisher=[[Railway Age]] |first=John |last=Thompson |date=January 5, 2018 |accessdate=January 11, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180112160104/http://www.railwayage.com/index.php/passenger/light-rail/the-car-that-saved-torontos-streetcars.html |archive-date=January 12, 2018 |url-status=l