o the type of wheel we now see on the CLRVs, itself a descendent of the PCC design. |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180116081325/https://stevemunro.ca/2007/10/21/a-short-history-of-the-clrv/ |archive-date=January 16, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"TTC-2009-02-18\">{{cite web |url=https://www.ttc.ca/TTC_Accessibility/Public_Forum_on_Accessible_Transit/2009/Accessible_Transit_Services_Plan_2008_Status_Report_and_Stat.jsp |title=Accessible Transit Services Plan: 2008 Status Report, and Status of Accessibility Standards |publisher=[[Toronto Transit Commission]] |date={{date|2009-02-18|mdy}} |accessdate={{date|2018-10-30|mdy}} |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181031052725/https://www.ttc.ca/TTC_Accessibility/Public_Forum_on_Accessible_Transit/2009/Accessible_Transit_Services_Plan_2008_Status_Report_and_Stat.jsp |archive-date=October 31, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Torontoist-2007-12-28\">{{cite web |url=https://torontoist.com/2007/12/hero_ttc_automa/ |title=Hero: TTC Automated Announcements |publisher=The Torontoist |first=Marc |last=Lostracco |date={{date|2007-12-28|mdy}} |accessdate={{date|2018-10-30|mdy}} |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181031091141/https://torontoist.com/2007/12/hero_ttc_automa/ |archive-date=October 31, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"TO-2016-02-25\">{{cite web |url=https://www.toronto.ca/legdocs/mmis/2016/ex/bgrd/backgroundfile-92670.pdf |title=2016 Accessibility Plan Status Report |publisher=[[City of Toronto government|City of Toronto]] |author=[[Toronto Transit Commission]] |date={{date|2016-02-25|mdy}} |accessdate={{date|2018-10-30|mdy}} |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181031091133/https://www.toronto.ca/legdocs/mmis/2016/ex/bgrd/backgroundfile-92670.pdf |archive-date=October 31, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"CityNews-2006-07-26\">{{cite web |url=https://toronto.citynews.ca/2006/07/26/first-air-conditioned-ttc-streetcar-unveiled/ |title=Firs