me streetcars, crushing others |work=MetroNews |first=Chris |last=Bateman |date=June 16, 2015 |accessdate=June 17, 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150620025517/http://metronews.ca/news/toronto/1399681/ttc-upgrading-some-streetcars-crushing-others/ |archive-date=June 20, 2015}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"TTC-2015-10-15\">{{cite news |url=https://www.ttc.ca/News/2015/October/1015_streetcar_rebuild.jsp/ |title=Newly-restored TTC streetcar enters service |newspaper=Toronto Transit Commission |date=October 15, 2015 |accessdate=October 22, 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161112085108/https://www.ttc.ca/News/2015/October/1015_streetcar_rebuild.jsp |archivedate=November 12, 2016}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"TheStar-2018-11-12\">{{cite news |url=https://www.thestar.com/news/gta/2018/11/12/toronto-pulls-plug-on-program-created-to-extend-life-of-older-streetcars-after-it-exceeds-budget-and-falls-short-of-target.html |title=TTC spent $26{{nbsp}}million to save 30 aging streetcars. But majority of the vehicles are still in the garage in need of more repairs |newspaper=[[Toronto Star]] |first=Ben |last=Spurr |date={{date|2018-11-12|mdy}} |accessdate={{date|2018-11-13|mdy}} |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181113042259/https://www.thestar.com/news/gta/2018/11/12/toronto-pulls-plug-on-program-created-to-extend-life-of-older-streetcars-after-it-exceeds-budget-and-falls-short-of-target.html |archive-date=November 13, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"BTO-2020-02-19\">{{cite web |url=https://www.blogto.com/city/2020/02/colourful-streetcar-new-home/ |title=Toronto's colourful streetcar has found a new home |publisher=blogTO |first=Mira |last=Miller |date={{date|2020-02-19|mdy}} |accessdate={{date|2020-03-06|mdy}} |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200306162400/https://www.blogto.com/city/2020/02/colourful-streetcar-new-home/ | archivedate={{date|2020-03-06|mdy}} }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"AIM-2020-donations\">{{cite web |url